1
00:00:18,018 --> 00:00:19,394
[Joe] Previously on You:

2
00:00:19,477 --> 00:00:23,064
[Goodwin] It's been three days
since the disappearance of Natalie Engler.

3
00:00:23,148 --> 00:00:24,858
-Falco.
-We found the ring.

4
00:00:24,941 --> 00:00:25,859
Okay.

5
00:00:25,942 --> 00:00:27,652
Love, this is my son, Theo.

6
00:00:27,736 --> 00:00:28,987
Didn't know you had a son.

7
00:00:29,070 --> 00:00:32,949
I'm still very unclear
as to why you decided to volunteer here.

8
00:00:33,033 --> 00:00:35,243
I'm at the hospital.
Henry has the measles.

9
00:00:35,326 --> 00:00:37,829
-Who do you think it was?
-Not closed yet, are you?

10
00:00:37,912 --> 00:00:40,248
Can't tell you
how sorry we are for exposing Henry.

11
00:00:40,331 --> 00:00:42,167
We hope you won't hold it against us.

12
00:00:42,250 --> 00:00:43,543
-Hey, Gil.
-Yep?

13
00:01:07,984 --> 00:01:10,403
[Joe]
Well, this came sooner than expected.

14
00:01:10,487 --> 00:01:13,406
The proverbial paint is hardly dry.

15
00:01:13,490 --> 00:01:14,908
Breathing.

16
00:01:14,991 --> 00:01:19,704
It's more than I can say for Natalie.
Meaning, you did the right thing.

17
00:01:22,457 --> 00:01:25,168
Controlled your impulses.

18
00:01:28,963 --> 00:01:31,007
So I won't be frustrated
with you, Love. No.

19
00:01:31,091 --> 00:01:32,217
This is growth,

20
00:01:32,300 --> 00:01:35,386
and it's important I show you
I recognize it--

21
00:01:35,470 --> 00:01:37,388
No. Appreciate it.

22
00:01:37,472 --> 00:01:41,309
I'll set aside the fact that we're using
our son's baby monitor as surveillance.

23
00:01:41,392 --> 00:01:43,686
It's twisted but smart.

24
00:01:43,770 --> 00:01:44,938
[Gil groaning]

25
00:01:46,481 --> 00:01:48,399
[Joe] Hey, Gil. Hey, buddy.

26
00:01:49,776 --> 00:01:50,819
Hey there.

27
00:01:51,653 --> 00:01:52,779
Hey.

28
00:01:52,862 --> 00:01:54,030
She hit me.

29
00:01:54,989 --> 00:01:56,407
[groaning]

30
00:01:56,491 --> 00:01:57,325
I'm so sorry.

31
00:01:57,408 --> 00:01:59,410
"Slipped and hit your head" is
off the table.

32
00:01:59,494 --> 00:02:01,287
Your wife. She knocked me out.

33
00:02:01,371 --> 00:02:03,081
[Joe] Can't say it was a shock.

34
00:02:03,164 --> 00:02:04,332
I was shocked.

35
00:02:04,415 --> 00:02:07,502
I said, "Gil? Nice guy Gil?"

36
00:02:07,585 --> 00:02:09,671
'Course she told me what you said.

37
00:02:10,755 --> 00:02:15,218
Not that it justified what she did.
The thing is, if you could have seen...

38
00:02:16,344 --> 00:02:19,013
what she went through
in the hospital with our baby...

39
00:02:19,806 --> 00:02:20,640
Here.

40
00:02:25,395 --> 00:02:29,065
Still, she should not have done this.

41
00:02:29,149 --> 00:02:30,316
That's for sure.

42
00:02:34,571 --> 00:02:38,241
It's a proofing room.
Something about temperature and humidity.

43
00:02:38,324 --> 00:02:42,954
Keeps the dough from getting a tough skin.
I'm not sure I understand any of it.

44
00:02:43,037 --> 00:02:45,290
That's Margaret with her gardening.

45
00:02:46,166 --> 00:02:48,626
Seeds and soil pH and...

46
00:02:48,710 --> 00:02:51,129
[Joe] Friendly chatter's
a reflex with this guy.

47
00:02:51,212 --> 00:02:55,175
You may have assaulted the one person
who might give us a pass for this.

48
00:02:55,258 --> 00:02:57,760
Love and I are very embarrassed.

49
00:02:57,844 --> 00:03:00,346
Is there any chance
we could keep this between us?

50
00:03:00,430 --> 00:03:03,850
We will not tell a soul
how you recklessly endangered our son.

51
00:03:03,933 --> 00:03:06,853
-I don't know I would put it like that.
-No? How?

52
00:03:07,979 --> 00:03:10,690
Well, it's just-- No judgment.

53
00:03:10,773 --> 00:03:14,277
But to dose an infant
with chemicals we know nothing about?

54
00:03:14,360 --> 00:03:16,487
-I mean, I call that reckless.
-Hmm.

55
00:03:16,571 --> 00:03:20,158
Actually, your son has naturally
gained immunity, so...

56
00:03:20,950 --> 00:03:22,493
I'd say it was beneficial.

57
00:03:22,577 --> 00:03:23,661
[knuckles cracking]

58
00:03:26,831 --> 00:03:28,333
You know what? I'm sorry.

59
00:03:28,416 --> 00:03:31,502
-I'm sorry, I get carried away.
-No, no, no.

60
00:03:33,546 --> 00:03:35,048
You might be right, yeah.

61
00:03:35,965 --> 00:03:38,885
-Our child is fine.
-Yeah.

62
00:03:41,512 --> 00:03:42,597
Here.

63
00:03:49,520 --> 00:03:51,022
Here, let me help you up.

64
00:03:53,107 --> 00:03:54,067
[Gil grunts]

65
00:03:54,150 --> 00:03:55,068
Ooh.

66
00:03:59,906 --> 00:04:02,242
So, what do you say, bygones?

67
00:04:08,873 --> 00:04:09,791
Okay.

68
00:04:10,917 --> 00:04:13,086
Sure. Bygones.

69
00:04:16,547 --> 00:04:17,548
[Joe] He's lying.

70
00:04:17,632 --> 00:04:19,926
-Are you absolutely sure?
-[Gil] I'm cool!

71
00:04:20,009 --> 00:04:22,011
I'm cool. Let me out, please?

72
00:04:22,095 --> 00:04:24,138
No doubt. He'll go straight to the police.

73
00:04:24,222 --> 00:04:26,766
-Fuck.
-Guys, let's be grown-ups about this!

74
00:04:26,849 --> 00:04:28,810
-Now what?
-Come on!

75
00:04:41,114 --> 00:04:43,574
Here we go. Coming in hot, Henry. Hey.

76
00:04:43,658 --> 00:04:48,162
[sputtering] Got to bank to the left.
Here. Open. There we go.

77
00:04:48,246 --> 00:04:51,291
Peek in our window,
you see your typical suburban family

78
00:04:51,374 --> 00:04:52,792
having a typical morning.

79
00:04:52,875 --> 00:04:54,711
You know, it can be blissful...

80
00:04:55,336 --> 00:04:57,922
watching our son discover
the pleasures of sweet potatoes.

81
00:04:58,006 --> 00:04:59,090
All I really need.

82
00:04:59,173 --> 00:05:00,425
I did have a thought.

83
00:05:02,802 --> 00:05:04,804
Mutually-assured destruction.

84
00:05:04,887 --> 00:05:08,099
Get something that he doesn't want
anyone else to know about

85
00:05:08,182 --> 00:05:10,143
and he can't expose us.

86
00:05:11,477 --> 00:05:15,106
-He opens his mouth, we open ours.
-Worked for me once before.

87
00:05:15,189 --> 00:05:17,108
It would have, Benji.

88
00:05:17,191 --> 00:05:20,320
-He may look like a choirboy...
-So did Dahmer.

89
00:05:34,876 --> 00:05:37,378
[Joe] A plan in place,
a Monday's worth of returns.

90
00:05:37,462 --> 00:05:41,924
I got lots of time to learn what Gil's
hiding behind the Mr. Rogers persona.

91
00:05:43,718 --> 00:05:47,472
Okay. All right. So Google
out of my boss's eagle-eyeline.

92
00:05:48,264 --> 00:05:50,641
Kids are gonna commit hara-kiri.

93
00:05:50,725 --> 00:05:53,144
No child sacrifice in the library, please.

94
00:05:53,227 --> 00:05:55,855
Gil is MIA. He was our reader today,

95
00:05:55,938 --> 00:05:58,274
and I told Lansing
I'd run the boys to the dentist.

96
00:05:58,358 --> 00:06:01,361
-[Joe] He did not just say "Gil."
-That's so not like Gil.

97
00:06:02,028 --> 00:06:04,238
He's their favorite. Man's a saint.

98
00:06:04,322 --> 00:06:07,658
[Joe] Except for that one dark thing
about him that Dante knows?

99
00:06:07,742 --> 00:06:10,661
You know better than that.
Not even the saints were saints.

100
00:06:10,745 --> 00:06:12,705
Hey, sorry. I couldn't help but overhear.

101
00:06:12,789 --> 00:06:14,624
-I could read to the kids.
-I've got it.

102
00:06:14,707 --> 00:06:15,708
Okay.

103
00:06:17,293 --> 00:06:21,005
Joe Goldberg? Hi.
Did I know you work here?

104
00:06:21,089 --> 00:06:23,549
[Joe] Did I know you had
your breasts enhanced in 2017?

105
00:06:23,633 --> 00:06:26,344
Vlogged your recovery
from Adderall addiction?

106
00:06:26,427 --> 00:06:28,679
Brother's a roadie
for 5 Seconds of Summer?

107
00:06:28,763 --> 00:06:29,889
Cool to post this?

108
00:06:34,435 --> 00:06:35,812
[Gil over phone] This is stupid!

109
00:06:36,562 --> 00:06:38,731
Hey, hello? Hey!

110
00:06:39,232 --> 00:06:41,943
-Hey, you--
-I could have one of everything.

111
00:06:42,860 --> 00:06:44,195
Well, I wouldn't tell.

112
00:06:44,278 --> 00:06:46,030
But my ass would.

113
00:06:47,407 --> 00:06:48,783
God, I envy you, Love.

114
00:06:48,866 --> 00:06:51,369
I have so many photo shoots,
next thing you know,

115
00:06:51,452 --> 00:06:53,913
people will be calling me "brave"
and then unfollowing

116
00:06:53,996 --> 00:06:56,666
'cause I'm no longer aspirational.
[chuckles]

117
00:06:56,749 --> 00:06:57,959
Mind if I post this?

118
00:06:58,042 --> 00:06:58,960
Oh.

119
00:06:59,627 --> 00:07:01,379
Perfect. Okay, ciao.

120
00:07:02,255 --> 00:07:03,172
Ciao.

121
00:07:04,173 --> 00:07:05,842
[door opens, then bells chiming]

122
00:07:08,928 --> 00:07:10,221
-Fuck.
-[Joe] Love, listen.

123
00:07:10,304 --> 00:07:12,890
[Love] That ring, it was supposed
to look like she left it there,

124
00:07:12,974 --> 00:07:15,476
then moved on,
but of course they want to look there.

125
00:07:16,561 --> 00:07:19,397
-What if we missed something else?
-We control what we can.

126
00:07:19,480 --> 00:07:20,898
We keep up appearances.

127
00:07:21,524 --> 00:07:24,235
We volunteer to help with the search.

128
00:07:25,319 --> 00:07:28,030
-God.
-It's gonna be okay.

129
00:07:29,407 --> 00:07:30,241
Okay.

130
00:07:31,659 --> 00:07:32,910
I'll see you at home.

131
00:07:37,165 --> 00:07:39,459
[Joe] A man in a cage is a problem.

132
00:07:39,542 --> 00:07:41,711
Few hundred citizens combing the woods

133
00:07:41,794 --> 00:07:43,880
where we buried
and exhumed Natalie Engler?

134
00:07:43,963 --> 00:07:45,381
Full-stop crisis.

135
00:07:49,760 --> 00:07:52,388
[Theo]
I don't understand why I would go to this!

136
00:07:52,472 --> 00:07:55,099
-[Matthew] Theo, can you be reasonable?
-You can't make me volunteer!

137
00:07:55,183 --> 00:07:59,770
-That's implied in the word "volunteer"--
-Theo! Keep your voice down.

138
00:07:59,854 --> 00:08:02,315
Dad, they're making you look pathetic.

139
00:08:03,274 --> 00:08:04,859
I am not going.

140
00:08:04,942 --> 00:08:08,905
When you're ready to talk like a person
above the age of 6, I'll be inside.

141
00:08:19,832 --> 00:08:22,919
Hey, was the idea to be so loud,
the whole neighborhood could hear?

142
00:08:24,045 --> 00:08:27,006
'Cause that was gauche.
You sounded like a brat.

143
00:08:27,089 --> 00:08:29,509
You little peeping Tom. You spying on me?

144
00:08:29,592 --> 00:08:30,760
[Love chuckles]

145
00:08:30,843 --> 00:08:33,095
What's up with all the dad theatrics?

146
00:08:33,971 --> 00:08:35,014
Um...

147
00:08:35,097 --> 00:08:38,851
So, apparently, Sherry Conrad
and her creepy little squad

148
00:08:38,935 --> 00:08:43,064
are teaming up with the cops
to go search some state park

149
00:08:43,147 --> 00:08:46,984
to, like, I don't know,
find Natalie out there stacking rocks?

150
00:08:47,860 --> 00:08:49,028
You don't want to join?

151
00:08:49,111 --> 00:08:52,657
I've been waiting
for this opportunity to join a cabal

152
00:08:52,740 --> 00:08:55,660
of soulless, bulimic yoga moms.
I think it's my calling.

153
00:09:03,751 --> 00:09:05,628
They're convinced that he killed her.

154
00:09:06,379 --> 00:09:10,091
I don't want him helping
the villagers sharpen their pitchforks.

155
00:09:12,927 --> 00:09:17,223
You should go. Optics are a thing.
If you don't go, both of you look bad.

156
00:09:18,224 --> 00:09:19,642
Hey, hey, hey.

157
00:09:20,393 --> 00:09:23,813
I will be your search buddy. Hmm?

158
00:09:23,896 --> 00:09:24,939
[gasps]

159
00:09:26,732 --> 00:09:28,401
Tie my shoes and everything?

160
00:09:29,277 --> 00:09:30,278
If necessary.

161
00:09:33,030 --> 00:09:34,490
Brat.

162
00:09:35,408 --> 00:09:37,910
Hey, you should get this fixed by the way.

163
00:09:42,832 --> 00:09:46,043
[Joe] This "Hands Across
Madre Linda" exercise in the woods

164
00:09:46,127 --> 00:09:48,170
has me dangerously distracted.

165
00:09:49,714 --> 00:09:53,593
What if we did leave something
for John and Betty Volunteer to find?

166
00:09:54,510 --> 00:09:57,305
But we weren't careless, were we?

167
00:09:57,388 --> 00:09:59,473
Focus! One thing at a time.

168
00:10:01,475 --> 00:10:04,103
Need to find Gil's fatal flaw.

169
00:10:05,229 --> 00:10:08,024
"Geology rocks." "Schist happens."

170
00:10:08,107 --> 00:10:11,444
If I've mined anything, it's that
"Rock Star" Professor Gil Brigham

171
00:10:11,527 --> 00:10:13,279
has a taste for geologist humor.

172
00:10:13,362 --> 00:10:16,032
Once taught at Burgess College
in Columbus, Ohio.

173
00:10:16,115 --> 00:10:19,076
Left in his second year. In October. Hmm.

174
00:10:19,160 --> 00:10:20,161
It's abrupt.

175
00:10:20,244 --> 00:10:22,913
Did he transgress with a co-ed?

176
00:10:22,997 --> 00:10:25,666
"Sophomore Burgess student
victim of campus attack."

177
00:10:25,750 --> 00:10:27,335
Could it be...?

178
00:10:28,502 --> 00:10:29,420
Hmm.

179
00:10:31,922 --> 00:10:34,925
Four hours in
and the only fault I can find

180
00:10:35,009 --> 00:10:36,719
is Gil's sense of humor.

181
00:10:36,802 --> 00:10:39,889
Spotless academic career, church,
a dedication to his kids so deep

182
00:10:39,972 --> 00:10:42,850
he may be the inspiration
for those World's Greatest Dad mugs.

183
00:10:42,933 --> 00:10:44,977
Never misses a game, a birthday--

184
00:10:45,061 --> 00:10:47,063
Look, he volunteers
at the children's ward--

185
00:10:47,146 --> 00:10:48,856
And shit! The library.

186
00:10:48,939 --> 00:10:50,441
Better account for today.

187
00:10:51,442 --> 00:10:55,613
Sorry to miss today. A little work crisis.

188
00:10:55,696 --> 00:10:57,990
Sorry to disappoint the kids.

189
00:10:58,074 --> 00:10:59,825
-[Marienne] Who are we stalking?
-Hey.

190
00:10:59,909 --> 00:11:02,411
-No, no, I'm just--
-You seen Peer Gynt?

191
00:11:02,495 --> 00:11:04,580
[Joe] Yes. In that I stole it for Ellie.

192
00:11:04,664 --> 00:11:07,958
Yeah, I may have taken it home for a read.

193
00:11:08,042 --> 00:11:11,420
You took a 2500-dollar book
that isn't supposed to leave?

194
00:11:11,504 --> 00:11:14,215
You know how when you know a rule exists,

195
00:11:14,298 --> 00:11:16,550
but you don't think it applies to you

196
00:11:16,634 --> 00:11:19,011
because you're quick
and careful, and you work here.

197
00:11:19,095 --> 00:11:23,015
For those of us who didn't grow up
with first editions for coasters--

198
00:11:23,099 --> 00:11:25,726
I'm sorry,
you think that I come from money?

199
00:11:25,810 --> 00:11:28,854
Look what you've done to me, Love.
I smell like the rich now.

200
00:11:28,938 --> 00:11:30,356
Just let me say this.

201
00:11:30,439 --> 00:11:32,983
There were no first editions
on the shelves growing up

202
00:11:33,067 --> 00:11:35,152
because there were no... shelves.

203
00:11:35,236 --> 00:11:37,863
-Right. You were poor.
-Practically homeless.

204
00:11:38,698 --> 00:11:41,492
A bookstore owner took me in
and let me work for free,

205
00:11:41,575 --> 00:11:44,120
and I slept in a cage in his basement.

206
00:11:45,121 --> 00:11:47,790
No, wait. Marienne, hang on.
Wait, I'm sorry.

207
00:11:47,873 --> 00:11:51,335
I'm sorry. Stop. That crossed the line.
It was an exaggeration.

208
00:11:51,419 --> 00:11:53,671
We straddled the poverty line
my entire childhood,

209
00:11:53,754 --> 00:11:57,049
and I escaped with books.

210
00:11:57,675 --> 00:11:58,884
I learned all about them,

211
00:11:58,968 --> 00:12:01,637
like you wanna know everything
about that one beautiful thing.

212
00:12:02,471 --> 00:12:05,391
It saves your miserable life.

213
00:12:07,309 --> 00:12:08,310
So I...

214
00:12:09,520 --> 00:12:12,273
I misjudged a little, maybe.

215
00:12:12,356 --> 00:12:15,735
Generally, my favorite apologies
are stiff and grudging...

216
00:12:17,278 --> 00:12:18,112
Fair.

217
00:12:19,029 --> 00:12:19,864
I'm sorry.

218
00:12:19,947 --> 00:12:21,031
Ah...

219
00:12:23,617 --> 00:12:26,996
And I guess I might have
to like you after all, Goldberg.

220
00:12:27,621 --> 00:12:29,373
-Perish the thought.
-Hmm.

221
00:12:30,332 --> 00:12:33,377
Since we're friends now,
what else did you take?

222
00:12:33,461 --> 00:12:35,504
[Joe] A Dickens, a Shelley,
a signed early Strand.

223
00:12:35,588 --> 00:12:36,672
-Nothing.
-Mm-hm.

224
00:12:36,756 --> 00:12:40,384
Make sure that's still true
when I look real hard tomorrow.

225
00:12:40,468 --> 00:12:41,302
Okay?

226
00:12:50,811 --> 00:12:53,314
-[Gil] Thought we had a deal!
-We did. I'm sorry.

227
00:12:53,397 --> 00:12:57,109
You know, you can't keep me in here
like some animal.

228
00:12:57,193 --> 00:13:01,739
People know that I was coming here.
So you can let me out or the police can.

229
00:13:01,822 --> 00:13:05,284
-When they come looking--
-No one's gonna save you. We--

230
00:13:06,660 --> 00:13:09,538
We already made excuses on your behalf.

231
00:13:10,414 --> 00:13:11,332
Uh...

232
00:13:11,415 --> 00:13:14,502
I'm sorry, Gil.
I want to let you out, man.

233
00:13:15,169 --> 00:13:16,712
I won't tell a soul.

234
00:13:16,796 --> 00:13:17,838
I promise.

235
00:13:17,922 --> 00:13:20,925
I told you, we can keep this between us.

236
00:13:24,428 --> 00:13:25,262
Say...

237
00:13:26,680 --> 00:13:28,390
we knew something about you.

238
00:13:28,474 --> 00:13:33,938
Something you really don't want
anyone to know.

239
00:13:36,190 --> 00:13:38,150
Right, I see.

240
00:13:38,234 --> 00:13:40,861
Okay, I keep your secret, you keep mine.

241
00:13:41,695 --> 00:13:44,865
And this time,
you'll keep your end of the deal?

242
00:13:44,949 --> 00:13:45,825
Yes.

243
00:13:46,784 --> 00:13:48,702
Okay. Okay.

244
00:13:50,579 --> 00:13:52,957
Just-- Give me a minute to think.

245
00:13:56,377 --> 00:13:57,211
I got it!

246
00:13:58,003 --> 00:13:58,963
Okay, listen.

247
00:14:01,257 --> 00:14:06,011
Couple years back, our church group went
to a festival for Christ in Vegas.

248
00:14:06,095 --> 00:14:09,473
